stylometry: The variables that must be considered when setting a level of safety stock are that the greater the variability in demand and lead time, the higher level of safety stock needed. We can set the desried service level, but the other numbers are variable and unprediciatible. We must weight the cost of holding vs. the probability of a stock out. The cost of holding is based upon how much it costs to keep invertory tied up (loss of interest, keeping inventory in a warehouse, etc.), and the probability of a stcok out is weighed upon the demand during lead time, and the loss of business when a stock out occurs. The fixed cost of ordering can also tilt the scale when making safety stock decisions. The purpose of safety stock is to reduce the probability of a stock-out. Safety stock equals the zscore of the desried service level, times the std dev of the demand during lead time.
